FR940304-2-00120 FR940304-2-00054 Determinations Regarding Eligibility To Apply for Worker Adjustment Assistance and NAFTA Transitional Adjustment Assistance In accordance with section 223 of the Trade Act of 1974, as amended, the Department of Labor herein presents summaries of determinations regarding eligibility to apply for trade adjustment assistance for workers (TA&hyph;W) issued during the period of February, 1994. In order for an affirmative determination to be made and a certification of eligibility to apply for worker adjustment assistance to be issued, each of the group eligibility requirements of section 222 of the Act must be met: (1) That a significant number or proportion of the workers in the workers' firm, or an appropriate subdivision thereof, have become totally or partially separated, (2) That sales or production, or both, of the firm or subdivision have decreased absolutely, and (3) That increases of imports of articles like or directly competitive with articles produced by the firm or appropriate subdivision have contributed importantly to the separations, or threat thereof, and to the absolute decline in sales or production. Negative Determinations for Worker Adjustment Assistance In each of the following cases the investigation revealed that criterion (3) has not been met. A survey of customers indicated that increased imports did not contribute importantly to worker separations at the firm. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,291; Simpson Timber Co., Korbel, CA TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,315; S & S Cutting, Pittston, PA TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,266; Owens Illinois, Inc., Huntington, WV TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,273; Erving Health Care, New Brunswick, NJ TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,333; CTS Connector Division, New Hope, MN In the following cases, the investigation revealed that the criteria for eligibility have not been met for the reasons specified. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,093; Galdco Services, Inc., Ira, TX The workers' firm does not produce an article as required for certification under section 222 of the Trade Act of 1974. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,336; Willamette Industrial Forms Div., Beaverton, OR Layoffs at the subject firm are attributable to a corporate decision to consolidate its operations resulting in the transfer of production from the subject plant in Beaverton, OR to another domestic plant. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,169; Wincup Holdings, Inc., Tinton Falls, NJ Increased imports did not contribute importantly to worker separations at the firm. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,144; Shiawassee Manufacturing Co., Owosso, MI The workers' firm does not produce an article as required for certification under section 222 of the Trade Act of 1974. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,302; Emerson Radio Corp., Princeton, IN The workers' firm does not produce an article as required for certification under section 222 of the Trade Act of 1974. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,468; Sensor Systems, Inc., Chatsworth, CA The investigation revealed that criterion (2) has not been met. Sales or production did not decline during the relevant period for certification. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,149; Duback Gas Co., Dubach, LA TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,149A; Endevco, Inc., Houston, TX TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,150; Duback Gas Co., (Clairborne Gas Plant), Lisbon, LA The investigation revealed that criterion (2) and criterion (3) have not been met. Sales or production did not decline during the relevant period. Increases of imports of articles like or directly competitive with articles produced by the firm or appropriate subdivision have not contributed importantly to the separations or threat thereof, and the absolute decline in sales or production. Affirmative Determinations for Worker Adjustment Assistance TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,213; Smead Manufacturing Co., Hastings, MN A certification was issued covering all workers separated on or after August 1, 1993. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,298; Lear Seating Corp., Morristown, TN A certification was issued covering all workers separated on or after November 11, 1992. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,363; The American Olean Tile Co., Inc., Lansdale, PA A certification was issued covering all workers separated on or after December 10, 1992. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,368; Gilligan & O'Malley, Latta, SC A certification was issued covering all workers separated on or after December 22, 1992. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,295; Nestle Beverage Co., Sunbury, OH A certification was issued covering all workers separated on or after November 23, 1992.
